[{"id":"b69528eb8e583b2c5bfe4b468053e144","from":"J. Epstein","from_email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to":"Emad Hanna","to_list":[{"name":"Emad Hanna","email":"ehanna@nysgmail.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"Re: Sketch","date":"2007-03-05T18:59:53.000Z","formatted_date":"Mar 5, 2007","formatted_time":"6:59 PM","body":"the question is what happens to the wind at the top of the windows, where it meets the overhang??  \n\n\n----- Original Message ----\nFrom: Emad Hanna <ehanna@nysgmail.com>\nTo: jeeproject@yahoo.com\nSent: Monday, March 5, 2007 8:34:36 AM\nSubject: FW: Sketch\n\n\nThe middle part which is the door will be one piece the top portion would be a window in a door and the bottom would have no window. He is not sure if they can make the whole door as a window.\n \nHow would you like to proceed?\n \nEmad Hanna\nProject Controller\nNES, LLC\n457 Madison Ave\nNew York, NY 10022\n'   (212) 891-6414\nFax (212) 750-2408\n\u203a ehanna@nysgmail.com\n \n\n\n\nFrom: Harris Glaser [mailto:harris@midnightboats.com] \nSent: Monday, March 05, 2007 11:22 AM\nTo: Emad Hanna\nSubject: Sketch\n \nEmad,\n \nThis is a rough sketch just so you understand what I\u2019m talking about.  \n \nThe enclosure would be attached vertically right onto the two consoles, this way we can have a door that is not two pieced, and vision won\u2019t be blurred.  Also, there are some restraints down the gunwales that would make it very difficult to achieve this enclosure if we were to make it slant forward.\n \n \nHarris Glaser\nVice President\nMidnight Express Powerboats\n \n4720 NW 15th. Ave\nUnit C\nFort Lauderdale, FL 33309\n \nwww.midnightboats.com\n \nOffice: 954-928-0280\nFax: 954-928-0288\nCell: 305-733-6202\n \n \n \nTHIS ELECTRONIC MAIL AND ANY ATTACHMENTS ARE INTENDED FOR THE ADDRESSEE ONLY.  IT CONTAINS INFORMATION THAT IS PRIVILEGED, CONFIDENTIAL OR OTHERWISE PROTECTED FROM DISCLOSURE.  ANY REVIEW, DISSEMINATION OR USE OF THIS TRANSMISSION OR ITS CONTENTS BY PERSONS OTHER THAN THE ADDRESSEE IS STRICTLY PROHIBITED.  IF YOU HAVE RECEIVED THIS E-MAIL IN ERROR, PLEASE NOTIFY THE SENDER IMMEDIATELY BY TELEPHONE OR RETURN E-MAIL, AND PERMANENTLY DELETE IT AND DESTROY ANY HARD COPY PRINTOUTS OF THIS TRANSMISSION.\n\n\n\nFrom: Harris Glaser [mailto:harris.glaser@gmail.com] \nSent: Monday, March 05, 2007 11:19 AM\nTo: Harris Glaser\nSubject:\n\n\n \n____________________________________________________________________________________\nNow that's room service!  Choose from over 150,000 hotels\nin 45,000 destinations on Yahoo! Travel to find your fit.\nhttp://farechase.yahoo.com/promo-generic-14795097","body_html":"<html><head><style type=\"text/css\"><!-- DIV {margin:0px;} --></style></head><body><div style=\"font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt\"><DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">the question is what happens to the wind at the top of the windows, where it meets the overhang??&nbsp; <BR><BR>\n<DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">----- Original Message ----<BR>From: Emad Hanna &lt;ehanna@nysgmail.com&gt;<BR>To: jeeproject@yahoo.com<BR>Sent: Monday, March 5, 2007 8:34:36 AM<BR>Subject: FW: Sketch<BR><BR>\n<STYLE>\n<!--\n _filtered {font-family:Tahoma;\npanose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;}\n _filtered {font-family:\"Wingdings 2\";\npanose-1:5 2 1 2 1 5 7 7 7 7;}\n _filtered {font-family:Webdings;\npanose-1:5 3 1 2 1 5 9 6 7 3;}\n/* Style Definitions */\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\n\t{margin:0in;\nmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\nfont-size:12.0pt;\nfont-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\na:link, span.MsoHyperlink\n\t{color:blue;\ntext-decoration:underline;}\na:visited, span.MsoHyperlinkFollowed\n\t{color:purple;\ntext-decoration:underline;}\nspan.EmailStyle17\n\t{\nfont-family:Arial;\ncolor:navy;}\nspan.EmailStyle18\n\t{\nfont-family:Arial;\ncolor:navy;}\n _filtered {\nmargin:1.0in 1.25in 1.0in 1.25in;}\ndiv.Section1\n\t{}\n-->\n</STYLE>\n\n